Remember that Richemont, owner of Cartier and Van Cleef &amp; Arpels, =E2=
=80=9Csmashed=E2=80=9D expectations?) Reading between the lines of the LVMH=
 press
release, it=E2=80=99s clear that Sephora once again absolutely murdered, wi=
th organic sales up 6 percent, and that the fashion and leather goods divis=
ion, despite some struggles, still made =E2=82=AC41 billion, with =E2=80=9C=
operating margin remaining at an exceptional level.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0<br/><br/=
>Sales increased in Europe and the U.S., partially making up for the contin=
