x;">Larroud=C3=A9=E2=80=99s accordioned supply chain dramatically reduced t=
he risk of a wholesale partner
ending up with shoes nobody wants. =E2=80=9CWe are able to produce in betwe=
en two and three weeks=E2=80=99 time,=E2=80=9D Marina told me. =E2=80=9CWhi=
ch is insane if you compare it to the major footwear brands. They take at l=
east six months, sometimes a year, to get a reorder in, right? So we really=
 changed the game in that sense.=E2=80=9D The strategy had other perks, too=
=2E =E2=80=9CIf they have a shoe that is n=
ot selling, and they decide to put=20=
that on a markdown, at the end of the day it=E2=80=99s jeopardizing our bra=
nd,=E2=80=9D Marina said. =E2=80=9CSo for us,
it=E2=80=99s better if we have access to see what performs, and then we&#39=
;re gonna produce more.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;=
">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Of course, there were =
setbacks as well. The company did more business in November 2024 than <em>a=
ll </em>of 2022, but the high volume led to shipping holdups, delayed refun=
ds, and uneven customer support. Most of the volume came from the company=
=E2=80=99s D.T.C. channels, but it was hard to contain. Some of those gripe=
s would
eventually find their way onto Larroud=C3=A9=E2=80=99s Instagram account.</=
p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;m=
argin-bottom:0px;">Indeed, small forecasting misses can result in meaningfu=
l delays. But rather than communicate those delays to consumers this past q=
uarter, it seems they just=E2=80=A6 hoped it would get better. Larroud=C3=
=A9 <em>did</em> offer credits to customers, but the resulting social media=
 comments were a mess. Since then, the company has been ramping up its cust=
omer
service=E2=80=94Marina and Ricardo were also jumping in to help handle comp=
laints themselves=E2=80=94and looking for additional support. In any event,=
 it could not have been a restful holiday for the couple.</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">Larroud=C3=A9=
=E2=80=99s growing pains highlight just how hard it is to reinvent the trad=
itional retail model. But the company=E2=80=99s also tackling the industry=
=E2=80=99s biggest headaches head-on. Yes, <em>yes</em>, they still need to=
 solve their operational
challenges, but the shift away from traditional wholesale could provide a n=
ew blueprint for inventory management. In an industry grappling with invent=
ory issues, delayed payments, and changing consumer expectations, their exp=
eriment is admirable. Whether or not they succeed, they=E2=80=99re showing =
the industry what the future of fashion retail could look like.</p></div>
